description:
After his 2007 tribute to teenagers, Ashtray Rock, Plaskett temporarily broke from his backing band, the Emergency, to record Three in Nova Scotia. The Triple-length album finds the Juno nominee in true singer/songwriter mode. While he plays most instruments throughout, members of Emergency pop up for special appearances, as do female backing vocals, who add an essential, playful element - especially to the classic-rocking first volume, which focuses on breakups (&quot;Through &amp; Through &amp; Through&quot;, &quot;Every Time You Leave&quot;). The second volume has a more somber, intimate, and acoustic feel - including the folky standout &quot;Shine On, Shine On, Shine On.&quot; It's remarkable that Plaskett keeps things so fresh across the album's 27 tracks; the closing number, &quot;On &amp; On &amp; On,&quot; is an easygoing confessional with high-school references echoing Ashtray Rock's wit. &lt;a href=&quot;
